{"phase":"product","detail":"thinking: ## Product Report — Issue #50: `prepareForSynthesis`\n\n### 1. What we're building\n\nA single integration-layer function, `prepareForSynthesis(text, maxLength)`, that composes three already-shipped utilities into the one call a caller actually wants: *\"clean this text and give me provider-sized pieces with word counts.\"* It normalizes raw input, splits into `maxLength`-bounded chunks, and annotates each chunk with its word count.\n\nThe new module (`apps\/web\/src\/lib\/prepare-for-synthesis.ts`) + its vitest suite (`apps\/web\/src\/lib\/prepare-for-synthesis.test.ts`) — nothing else.\n\n### 2. Existing building blocks (already shipped, only imported)\n\n| What | Where | Key contract |\n|---|---|---|\n| `chunkText(text, maxLength): string[]` | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/chunk-text.ts` | Trims input; returns `[]` for empty\/whitespace; throws if `maxLength <= 0`; every chunk `≤ maxLength`; chunks join to exact trimmed original. |\n| `normalizeText(text): string` | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/text-utilities\/normalize-text.ts` | Collapses all whitespace runs to single spaces, trims; returns `\"\"` for empty\/whitespace-only. |\n| `wordCount(text): number` | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/text-utilities\/word-count.ts` | Internally normalizes first, then splits on spaces; returns `0` for empty\/whitespace-only. |\n| Barrel re-exports all three | `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/text-utilities\/index.ts` | `export { normalizeText }`, `export { wordCount }`, `export { truncateWords }` |\n\n### 3. Composition semantics (acceptance criteria mapped to what already exists)\n\nThe composition is straightforward — each step is a direct delegation:\n\n1. **Normalize first:** `const normalized = normalizeText(text)` → collapses whitespace, trims. For empty\/whitespace input this yields `\"\"`.\n2. **Chunk second:** `const pieces = chunkText(normalized, maxLength)` — since `chunkText` also trims, feeding it already-normalized text is harmless. For `\"\"` input, `chunkText` returns `[]`. For `maxLength <= 0`, it throws.\n3. **Annotate each piece:** `pieces.map(text => ({ text, wordCount: wordCount(text) }))` — `wordCount` internally normalizes again (benign, already normalized), splits on spaces, returns count.\n\n**Empty\/whitespace path:** `normalizeText('   ')` → `\"\"` → `chunkText('', maxLength)` → `[]` → result `[]`. Naturally satisfied by delegation; no special-case branching needed.\n\n**maxLength ≤ 0 path:** Delegates to `chunkText`, which throws `'maxLength must be a positive number'`. Naturally satisfied.\n\n**Invariants** are inherited from `chunkText`: every chunk `≤ maxLength` (guaranteed by the chunker), and rejoining reproduces the normalized content in order (guaranteed by chunker's character-preserving algorithm).\n\n### 4. Module surface\n\n```ts\nexport interface SynthesisChunk {\n  text: string;\n  wordCount: number;\n}\n\nexport function prepareForSynthesis(\n  text: string,\n  maxLength: number,\n): SynthesisChunk[];\n```\n\nThe new file lives at `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/prepare-for-synthesis.ts`. Imports:\n- `{ chunkText }` from `.\/chunk-text`\n- `{ normalizeText, wordCount }` from `.\/text-utilities`\n\n### 5. Existing test patterns\n\nBoth existing test suites (`chunk-text.test.ts`, `text-utilities\/index.test.ts`) follow the same pattern:\n\n```ts\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { functionUnderTest } from '.\/module-path';\n\ndescribe('functionUnderTest', () => {\n  it('does something', () => {\n    expect(functionUnderTest(input)).toEqual(expected);\n  });\n});\n```\n\nVitest config (`apps\/web\/vitest.config.ts`) picks up `src\/**\/*.test.ts`, uses `jsdom` environment, globals enabled. Test run command: `npm run test` (root) → `vitest run` in apps\/web.\n\n### 6. Test coverage required\n\nPer acceptance criteria, the suite must cover:\n\n| Scenario | Expected behavior |\n|---|---|\n| Empty string `\"\"` | `[]` |\n| Whitespace-only `\"   \"` | `[]` |\n| Single chunk (under limit) | One `SynthesisChunk` with correct `wordCount` |\n| Multi-chunk splitting | Multiple chunks, each annotated |\n| Every chunk ≤ maxLength | Property check across varied inputs |\n| Chunks rejoined = normalized original | Content preservation invariant |\n| `maxLength <= 0` throws | `maxLength = 0`, `maxLength = -1` both throw |\n\n### 7. Build & verify\n\n- **Build:** `npm run build:web` — runs catalog publish script then `svelte-kit sync && vite build`\n- **Test:** `npm run test` — runs `vitest run` in apps\/web\n- **Language:** TypeScript (strict mode), ESM (`\"type\": \"module\"`)\n- **Framework:** SvelteKit app (but this module is framework-agnostic, pure TypeScript)\n\n### 8. Out of scope (explicitly)\n\n- Wiring into dispatch\/HTTP — this is a standalone helper\n- Provider-specific `maxLength` lookups — caller supplies it\n- Changing `chunkText`, `normalizeText`, `wordCount`, or the text-utilities barrel\n- Updating any barrel\/index file — the issue doesn't call for it\n\n### 9. Decision recorded","outcome":{"note":{}},"at":804599036.365582,"id":"50-625","ticketId":"50"}
